This paper is about building a speech synthesizer without any text or phonetic labels, which falls under the field of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also involves unsupervised learning and subword unit discovery, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper discusses evaluation metrics and machine learning models, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves speech processing and audio data, which could also fall under cs.SD.
